CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 26, 1955, pg. 27, reads: "Reflect Grief - John R. Brice (left) and Clyde Wheeler, two members of the trustee board of Wayman AME Church, Monessen, reflect grief as they explore the second-story room of the parsonage where the Rev. J. Edward Keys suffocated last Friday during a raging fire. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: John R. Brice and Clyde Wheeler standing in fire damaged room in parsonage of Wyman AME Church, Monessen
